snippet.title: What Happened to Danity Kane? | Beef with Diddy. Breakups & Makeups. 2021 Update
snippet.description:
If you are a fan of P. Diddy, you have probably heard of his superstar pop girl-group Danity Kane. Danity Kane developed on Diddy’s hit MTV Series Making The Band and stormed the charts. On paper they were perfect -- five gifted, iconic women coached by the talented, mega-famous Diddy with their roots in a hit reality MTV show.

The original lineup of the group consisted of  Aundrea Fimbres, Aubrey O’Day, Dawn Richard, Wanita “D Woods” Woodgette and Shannon Bex. They were the first girl group in Billboard history to consecutively debut two albums at #1 and are featured in the Guinness World Book of Records. With mega hits like Showstopper and Damaged, the ladies were multi – platinum, surrounded by drama and ready to take over the music industry. With such a promising start, how did they change from musical heroes to legends? What happened to Danity Kane? Watch now to find out.


Also watch What Happened To:
Diddy's Making Da Band 2 - https://youtu.be/smk7pJLx4EE
